            "content": "18-22kW Air-Cooled Generators: $10,500-14,500 installed\nMost popular size for SaddleBrooke homes (1,800-2,500 sq ft). Powers central AC, medical equipment, refrigeration, and essential circuits. Natural gas fuel provides unlimited runtime. Includes automatic transfer switch, concrete pad, electrical connections, gas line coordination, permits, and startup.\n\n24-26kW Air-Cooled Generators: $13,500-17,000 installed\nProvides true whole-home power for larger SaddleBrooke homes or those wanting zero circuit shedding during outages. Supports all major appliances simultaneously.\n\nAdd-Ons and Considerations:\n- Natural gas line extension: $800-2,400 (if gas service needs extending to generator location)\n- Propane tank installation: $1,500-3,500 (for homes without natural gas service)\n- Enhanced sound attenuation enclosure: $1,200-2,200 (for very close neighbors)\n- Extended warranty (10 years parts + labor): $800-1,400\n- Annual maintenance plan: $275-450/year (essential for reliable operation)\n\nWhat Affects Generator Costs:\n- Distance from natural gas service to installation location\n- Electrical panel condition (may require upgrade for proper integration)\n- Installation complexity (difficult access, landscaping considerations)\n- Local permit fees ($150-300 typically)\n- HOA approval process and requirements (some restrictions on placement/screening)\n\nValue Beyond Cost:\n- Home value increase: $12,000-18,000 for installed generator\n- Insurance premium reduction: 8-15% annual savings\n- Health protection: maintaining safe temperatures and medical equipment operation\n- Food/medication protection: preventing $400-800 losses during outages\n- Peace of mind: priceless for active adults and concerned family members"
