            "content": "Tucson experiences intense monsoon lightning activity July through September, with thousands of lightning strikes occurring throughout Pima County during each major storm system. Lightning strikes can directly hit homes, nearby power lines, or ground areas transmitting destructive voltage spikes through your electrical system, damaging or destroying electronics, appliances, and electrical components worth $15,000-25,000 in typical SaddleBrooke home. Without surge protection, a single lightning strike can instantly damage: large-screen TVs and home theater equipment ($3,000-8,000 replacement cost), refrigerators and freezers with electronic controls ($1,200-3,500), computer systems and networking equipment ($2,000-5,000), garage door openers and smart home devices ($800-2,400), HVAC control boards and thermostats ($600-2,000), washer/dryer electronic controls ($400-1,600), and medical equipment and mobility devices (potentially irreplaceable)."
