            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "As mobility and dexterity change with age, strategic electrical modifications enhance accessibility and support aging in place for SaddleBrooke residents. Our accessibility electrical services help you maintain independence and safety in your retirement home. Rocker Switch Upgrades: Traditional toggle switches require precise pinching and flipping motions challenging for arthritic hands. Large rocker switches (paddle-style) operate with simple palm pressure (no pinching or gripping required), accommodate diminished dexterity and hand strength, and provide larger target area for activation (easier for those with vision changes). Rocker switch upgrades cost $45-75 per switch (material and labor) for typical residential installation. Upgrading critical switches (bedrooms, bathrooms, main living areas—typically 12-20 switches) costs $540-1,500 and dramatically improves daily accessibility. Illuminated Switches and Outlets: Switches and outlets with built-in LED locator lights (glowing ring or indicator) are visible in darkness (finding switches at night without fumbling), consume minimal energy (less than 1 watt per switch), and provide subtle nighttime navigation aid without bright nightlights. Illuminated switch/outlet upgrades cost $55-85 per location and are particularly valuable in bedrooms, hallways, and bathrooms where nighttime use is common."
